DATA CLOUD
Publish History of Your Activation

In Data Cloud, view the activation history to see when and how segments were published. For segments published to a Marketing Cloud Engagement activation target, additional columns appear in the activation history to provide more details. View the same publish history details in a segment record.

Find and view the activation history from Activations tab in Data Cloud.

General Activation History

HEADER	DESCRIPTION
Segment	Number of profiles in your segment
Activation	Number of profiles sent to your activation target
Last Publish Completed	Most recent date and time when your segment was published; value is blank for unpublished segments
Publish Type	How a segment was published
Publish Status	Status of a segment

Marketing Cloud Engagement Activation History

HEADER	DESCRIPTION
Segment	Number of profiles in your segment
Activation	Number of profiles sent to your activation target
Accepted	Number of profiles accepted by Marketing Cloud Engagement
Rejected	Number of profiles rejected by Marketing Cloud Engagement and the reasons why they were rejected
Target Profiles	Number of active profiles in the Marketing Cloud Engagement data extension
Last Publish Completed	Most recent date and time when your segment was published; value is blank for unpublished segments
Publish Type	How a segment was published through full or incremental refresh. Full refresh updates all the records in the segment. Incremental refresh updates only the changed records from the last refresh
Publish Status	

Status of a segment

Success: Segment published to Marketing Cloud Engagement
Segment Error: Failed to run the segment
Activation Error: Failed to generate the activation payload to the target
Queued: Waiting to process with the Marketing Cloud API
Partner Processing: The API is being processed before storing data in the data extension
Partner Error: Failed to store data in the data extension
